{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Let d = 11, X = [0, 2π], Z = [0, 2π], σ 2 = 0.1, f (x) = (sin(x), sin(2x),..., sin((d -1)x)), g(z) = (sin(z), sin(2z),..., sin((d -1)z)), and let P, Q be two orthogonal(d -1) × (d -1) matrices.",
    "Define v: X → R d-1 and u: Z → R d-1 as v(x) = P f (x) and u(z) = Qg(z).",
    "We set T = 1 Z ⊗ 1 X + d-1 i=1 σ i u i ⊗ v i.",
    "(X, Z) is jointly sampled with rejection sampling.",
    "Z, X are uniform on [0, 2π] and X given Z admits T as conditional expectation operator."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}